Act NOW to beat 10Huge hikes are predicted this year, but you can lock in today's
prices EVEN IF YOU'RE NOT AT RENEWAL ( # )

Car insurance prices have dropped 40years, according to the AA. But bumpy roads could lie ahead as,
due to more whiplash claims, its latest index predicts an
increase of up to 8now to grab a deal before the surge.

* The 5 key steps to cutting car insurance costs. There's no one
cheapest insurer, so you need a method to discover your winner.
Our full cheap car insurance ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/ ) system has
every trick in the book. Yet if you just want it quick & dirty,
here are the key five.

1. Combine the right comparison sites. They don't all cover the
same insurers, so combining them gives a wider coverage spread.
We currently assess the top order as a) MoneySup* ( http://www.moneysupermarket.com/car-insurance/?Source=MSE ) b)
Confused* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/4fb28432 ) c)
CompareTM ( http://www.comparethemarket.com/car-insurance/ ). See
full combine comparison sites ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/#comparison )
info.
2. Check insurers comparisons miss. Biggies Aviva* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/40185edc ), Direct Line* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/70fd449b ) & Zurich ( http://www.zurich.co.uk/car/ ) are missed, as are special deals ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/#hotdeals ).
3. More than one car at home? Check Admiral multicar* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/38865c73 ) & other
discounts at Churchill* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/9ee06f18 ), Direct Line* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/a04058dd ) & Privilege* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/b5e11fe9 ).
4. Three counter-logical savings - use trial & error. a) Try
adding a responsible 2nd driver ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/#responsible ) -
insurers can see it as cing risk; b) Use the car insurance
job picker ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/insurance/car-insurance-job-picker/ ) to tweak your job description; c)Don't assume 3rd party's
cheapest ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/#assumethird ),
the mere fact you select comprehensive cover can lower your risk
profile and possibly your price.
5. Beware paying monthly. They usually just loan the cash at a
high APR. Often paying by 0
As @surleydev says: "Just renewed, saved £1,232 by adding
parents, changing supplier & paying for the year."

* Lock in a price even if you're not at renewal. Those renewing
can just follow the tips above. If not, with price rises
predicted, check anyway if a better policy's available. If one
is, unless you've claimed, for a c.£50 fee you can usually cancel
existing cover and get a refund for the rest of the year, though
you won't earn the year's no claims.

- Renewal within 2mths? Cancellation fees would likely eat any
savings, yet there's another trick. Aviva* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/40185edc ), Post Office* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/b2fbb6b7 ) & LV* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/b43f7734 ) quotes last 60
days, so grab them now in case they rise. More policies with long
quotes in lock in a rate ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/#lock ).

