Are you earning 6Don't let cash drip away in 2015 - check your rates NOW. Speedy
tips to earn max interest on every single penny
( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/savings/which-saving-account )Savings rates have been depressingly depressed for the last year
and there's no sign of that abating. Yet there are few chinks of
light - you CAN earn more if you know what you're doing. Check
what you're getting then compare it to...

* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/savings/which-saving-account )
3to switch, a few bank accounts' in-credit rates smash standard
ISAs & savings. Santander 123* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/4d519365 ) pays 3£3k-£20k (there's a £2/mth fee but it's usually covered by bills
cashback). For lesser amounts TSB Classic* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/c43a066c ) is 5£2k. Full list in Best Bank Accounts ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/banking/compare-best-bank-accounts ) or read our 5for how to open multiple accounts to max it.
* 6some 'regular savings accounts' pay very high interest but on
relatively small sums. New & existing First Direct ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/savings/best-regular-savings-accounts#firstdirect ) customers (you get £125 to switch) can put £25-£300/mth in at
6all' deal is Leeds BS's ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/savings/best-regular-savings-accounts#leeds ) 3.05withdrawal and keep it after). Full help in Top Regular Savings ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/savings/best-regular-savings-accounts ).
* Top cash ISA - 2.4account where you don't pay tax on the interest. You can put up
to £15,000 in every tax year. Once in, it stays tax-free year
after year.
Our top pick's Coventry BS's ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/savings/best-cash-isa#manipulate ) 2.4early by closing it and lose just 120 days' interest. Which
means after 1yr you'd have earnt equiv 1.6after 3yrs 2.1Top Cash ISAs ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/savings/best-cash-isa ) & Cash
ISA Transfers ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/savings/cash-isa-transfers ).
* Top 1.85Bank ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/savings/savings-accounts-best-interest#oneyearfixed ) pays 1.85* Over 65? Earn 4our Pensioner Bonds - good for me? ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/savings/pensioner-bonds ) guide. 

