    <p class="bookgiveawaybox" style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 22px;"><a href="http://forums.moneysavingexpert.com/showthread.php?p=67354604&amp;utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=forum&amp;utm_content=2#post67354604" class="headline" style="color: #136C82; font-family: 'Segoe UI',sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-weight: normal; text-transform: uppercase;">MONEY MORAL DILEMMA</span><br /> 
      Should I remind tradesman to cash my cheque?</a><br />

      <em>This week's MoneySaver who wants advice asks...</em> Over two months ago a tradesman came to my property and did a good job, for which I gave him a cheque for &pound;69. So far the cheque has not been drawn on my bank account. Should I get in touch and remind him, or trust that he will find it and deposit it before it expires? <strong>Enter  the Money Moral Maze:</strong> <a href="http://forums.moneysavingexpert.com/showthread.php?p=67354604&amp;utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=forum&amp;utm_content=3#post67354604" target="_blank" style="color: #136c82;">Should I remind tradesman to cash my cheque?</a> | <a href="mailto:mmd@moneysavingexpert.com" style="color: #136c82;"> Suggest an MMD</a> | <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/shopping/chat-tips-gold?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=shopping&amp;utm_content=4#mmd" target="_blank" style="color: #136c82;">View Past MMDs</a></p>
	  
	    <p class="greathuntbox" style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 22px;"><a href="http://forums.moneysavingexpert.com/showthread.php?p=67354703&amp;utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=forum&amp;utm_content=5#post67354703" class="headline" style="color: #136C82; font-family: 'Segoe UI',sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-weight: normal; text-transform: uppercase;">THE GREAT HUNT</span><br />
        Breathing new life into otherwise worthless items for use around the home<br />
    </a>We want to tap MoneySavers' collective knowledge on  ways you've turned things you no longer need and can't sell (think CD racks, cassette tapes, items you've ripped out of a property you're fixing up, etc) into useful things you use around your home or perhaps even pieces of furniture. <strong>Share yours/read others':</strong> <a href="http://forums.moneysavingexpert.com/showthread.php?p=67354703&amp;utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=forum&amp;utm_content=6#post67354703" style="color: #136c82;">Breathing new life into otherwise worthless items for use around the home</a><strong> Past topics: </strong> <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/shopping/chat-tips-gold?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=shopping&amp;utm_content=7#hunts" style="color: #136c82;">View all</a></p>


    
    <p class="flightcheckerbox" style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 22px;"><a href="http://www.ryanair.com/en/redirect/2/wintergetaway/2/5/44/" class="headline" target="_blank" style="color: #136C82; font-family: 'Segoe UI',sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-weight: normal; text-transform: uppercase;">CHEAP FLIGHT SALES ALERT</span><br />    
Airline:<em> Ryanair </em>Price:<em> Flights from &pound;19.99 one-way </em>Ends:<em> </em>Sun 15 Feb<br />
    </a>Our pick this week is <a href="http://www.ryanair.com/en/redirect/2/wintergetaway/2/5/44/" style="color: #136c82;">Ryanair's</a>  sale that ends  Sun 15 Feb, with prices  including all non-optional taxes &amp; charges. It's for flights until Tue 31 Mar on selected routes. You must book 14 days in advance of travel. We've found  flights for even less than &pound;19.99; for example, London Stansted-Tours for &pound;14.99. <strong>Extra charges warning: </strong>Avoid payment and check-in charges - see the <span><a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/travel/beat-budget-airline-charges?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=travel&amp;utm_content=8" style="color: #136c82;">Budget Airline Fee Fighting</a> guide. <strong>Related: </strong><a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/travel/cheap-flights?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=travel&amp;utm_content=9" style="color: #136c82;">Cheap Flights</a>, <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/travel/cheap-hotels?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=travel&amp;utm_content=10" style="color: #136c82;">Cheap Hotels</a>, <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/cards/cheaper-spending-overseas?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=cards&amp;utm_content=11" style="color: #136c82;">Spending Abroad</a>, <a href="http://travelmoney.moneysavingexpert.com/?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=travelmoney&amp;utm_content=12" target="_blank" style="color: #136c82;">Cheap Currency</a>, <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/insurance/cheap-travel-insurance?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=msccontent&amp;utm_term=06-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=insurance&amp;utm_content=13" style="color: #136c82;">Travel Insurance</a></span></p>



